B. Earthquake centers in the region occur at shallow depths.
- Earthquakes at shallow depths are more characteristic of transform boundaries, where the plates are sliding past each other horizontally. If the earthquake centers are at shallow depths, it would support the initial determination that the region is a transform plate boundary.

